      <description>&lt;img src=&#34;ali-calligraphy-lion.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;Ali calligraphy lion&#34; style=&#34;max-width: 300px; display: block; margin: 0 auto; border-radius: 8px;&#34;&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“People are of two kinds: either your brothers in faith or your equals in humanity.”&lt;br&gt;
— Imam Ali&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’ve been reading &lt;em&gt;Ali: Elixir of Love&lt;/em&gt;, and this line struck me with its timeless moral clarity. It captures a universality that bridges faith and human dignity — something I think the modern world desperately needs to rediscover (more reflections coming soon.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
